svg.metadata: Created by FontForge 20161116 at Tue May 14 20:10:16 2013 By Jimmy Warting Helvetica (Latin for Swiss) has the objective and functional style which was associated with Swiss typography in the 1950s and 1960s. It is perfect for international correspondence: no ornament, no emotion, just clear presentation of information. Helvetica is still one of the best selling sans-serif fonts.
